                                <geo>51.884656, -3.236375</geo></origPlace>
                            <origDate></origDate>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance type="found" when="1922">Also known as the Llygadwy Stone, the stone stands in a field on the east side of <placeName>Bwlch</placeName>. The possibility that this stone once bore an ogham inscription was suggested by Macalister in 1922 and again in 1945. 
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed">In situ.
                        </provenance>
