            <div type="commentary">
                <p>According to Morgan (1983: 43), the stone may have been a lost monastic marker and that <q>the smooth-sided form of the stone, its rubbing-post function and the evidence of quarrying to the south might indicate a postmedieval date</q>. Redknap and Lewis (2007, 542) note that the name of the stone <q><foreign xml:lang="cy">Llygadwy</foreign> (earlier <foreign xml:lang="wlm">Llygadyw</foreign>, possibly <foreign xml:lang="owl">Llygad Duw</foreign>, 'eye of God') is derived from a nearby ruin, which appears on OS maps with this name</q> (Redknap and Lewis 2007, 542).</p>
            </div>
